<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-23T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="585" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2205: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bilbao</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chapman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bilbao</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-23T10:00:00+00:00">July 23, 1936—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 23—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Bilbao virtually in state siege, food shortage very likely to bring
                                about looting since authorities are not in a position to prevent it.
                                American citizens having no assurance protection, request that war
                                vessel take women and children as soon as possible.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chapman</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>